# LiberFi SDK Source Location

The source code for liberfi.io related components (React SDK) is located at `../react-sdk` relative to this project.

When investigating or modifying liberfi.io component internals, look for the corresponding source files under the `../react-sdk` directory.

# LiberFi SDK Version Update Rules

When updating `@liberfi.io/*` SDK versions in `apps/web/package.json`, you MUST also update the corresponding `peerDependencies` and `devDependencies` in all workspace packages under `packages/`. Specifically:

1. **Switch npm registry to the official source** before installing. `@liberfi.io/*` packages are published on the official npm registry.
   - Prefer `nrm use npm` if `nrm` is available.
   - Otherwise run `npm config set registry https://registry.npmjs.org/`.
2. Search all `packages/*/package.json` for any `@liberfi.io/*` references in both `peerDependencies` and `devDependencies`.
3. Update `peerDependencies` versions (using `>=` range) to match the new SDK version.
4. Update `devDependencies` versions (using `^` range) to match the new SDK version.
5. **Sync `@chainstream-io/sdk` version**: Check the `@chainstream-io/sdk` version used by `@liberfi.io/client` (inspect its `package.json` in `node_modules/@liberfi.io/client/package.json`), then update `@chainstream-io/sdk` in all `apps/*/package.json` and `packages/*/package.json` that reference it to match that version.
6. Run `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile` after all updates to sync the lockfile.
7. **Switch npm registry back to taobao mirror** after installation completes.
   - Prefer `nrm use taobao` if `nrm` is available.
   - Otherwise run `npm config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com/`.
